<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-15012] Camel-Http: Endpoint parameters proxyHost and proxyPort are ignored</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-15012</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The&#160;&lt;tt&gt;proxyHost&lt;/tt&gt; and&#160;&lt;tt&gt;proxyPort&lt;/tt&gt; query parameters&#160;are ignored by the camel-http compoment. They probably should be handled in &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.camel.component.http.HttpComponent#configureHttpProxy&lt;/tt&gt;. Right now that method only handles &lt;tt&gt;proxyAuthHost&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;proxyAuthPort&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using those query parameters seems to be the workaround, too, as &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.camel.component.http.ProxyHttpClientConfigurer&lt;/tt&gt; makes no distinction between authentication and non-authenticating proxies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relates to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-10216&quot; title=&quot;Camel-Http4: Endpoint parameters proxyHost and proxyPort are ignored&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-10216&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-10216&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
